    • Field Detail

      • pixelData

        public java.nio.ByteBuffer pixelData
        The pixel data of the image. The data is single channel grey-scale with 8-bits per pixel.

      • width

        public int width
        The width in pixels of the image. This can be different than QLDeviceInfo.sensorWidth if downsampling is used.

      • height

        public int height
        The height in pixels of the image. This can be different than QLDeviceInfo.sensorHeight if downsampling is used.

      • timestamp

        public double timestamp
        The timestamp of the frame in milliseconds.

      • gain

        public int gain
        The gain value of the image.

      • frameNumber

        public int frameNumber
        A number to identify a frame. Checking for non consecutive numbers from frame to frame can determine if a frame was lost.

      • roi

        public QLRectInt roi
        Information describing the location and size of the region of interest. If the device is not in region of interest mode then the x and y values will be zero and the width and height values will equal the width and height of the entire image.

      • scaleFactor

        public double scaleFactor
        The scale used for downsampling this image.
